entry.p: Data Group: CDS V6-2 Type 001 - CDS Interchange Header

entry.p: One per Commissioning Data Set record submitted to the Secondary_Uses_Service.
Multiple Commissioning Data Set Messages may be submitted in a single Commissioning Data Set Interchange.

p.b: To carry the details of the Patient Pathway.
the personal details of the Patient (the Baby). See Note: S3 in Commissioning Data Set Business Rules.
One of the following DATA GROUPS must be used:
DATA GROUP: WITHHELD IDENTITY STRUCTURE (Birth Episode) Must be used where the Commissioning Data Set record has been anonymised
Must be used where the NHS NUMBER STATUS INDICATOR CODE
Must be used for all other values of the NHS NUMBER STATUS INDICATOR CODE
To carry the characteristics of the Patient (the Baby).
To carry the Patient's General Medical Practitioner and the General Practice details.
To carry the details of the Pregnancy.

entry.p: Data Group: ANTENATAL CARE - ACTIVITY CHARACTERISTICS

p.b: To carry the details of the Antenatal Care.

entry.p: Data Group: ANTENATAL CARE - PERSON GROUP (RESPONSIBLE CLINICIAN)

p.b: To carry the details of the General Medical Practitioner responsible for the Antenatal Care.

entry.p: Data Group: ANTENATAL CARE - LOCATION GROUP - DELIVERY PLACE INTENDED

p.b: To carry the details of the Intended Delivery Location.
To carry the details of the Labour/Delivery.
To carry the details of the Service Agreement.

entry.p: Data Group: BIRTH OCCURRENCE - ACTIVITY CHARACTERISTICS

p.b: To carry the details of the Birth Occurrence.

entry.p: Data Group: BIRTH OCCURRENCE PERSON IDENTITY - MOTHER

p.b: To carry the Identity details of the Baby's Mother. See Note: S3 in Commissioning Data Set Business Rules.
One of the following DATA GROUPS must be used:
Must be used where the Commissioning Data Set record has been anonymised
Must be used where the NHS_NUMBER_STATUS_INDICATOR_CODE_(MOTHER)
Must be used for all other values of the NHS_NUMBER_STATUS_INDICATOR_CODE_(MOTHER)

entry.p: Data Group: DATA GROUP: DELIVERY OCCURRENCE - OVERSEAS VISITOR STATUS AT CDS ACTIVITY DATE GROUP

p.b: To carry the details of the Overseas Visitor Status of the Mother.

entry.p: Data Group: DATA GROUP: BIRTH OCCURRENCE - LOCATION GROUP - DELIVERY PLACE ACTUAL

p.b: To carry the details of the Actual Delivery Location.
